                                                                    <div class="moto-widget-text-content moto-widget-text-editable">
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“Whoever keeps the fig tree will eat its fruit; So he who waits on his master will be honored.
                                                                            As in water face reflects face, So a man’s heart reveals the man.”<b> Proverbs 27:18-19 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“being confident of this very thing, that He who has begun a good work in you will complete it until the day of Jesus Christ;”
                                                                            <b>Philippians 1:6 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">On the 10th of this month we started our journey assessing our perception of God. Over the past 13 days we briefly examined twelve attributes of God with the hope of reinforcing, strengthening and solidifying our perspective of God and how He desires us to freely surrender all of ourselves into His hand.  To behold the true perspective of Who He is, that we might not be deceived.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“As in water face reflects the face, so the heart of man reflects that man’s character.  “But we all, with unveiled face, beholding as in a mirror the glory of the Lord, are being transformed into the same image from glory to glory, just as by the Spirit of the Lord.”
                                                                            <b>Proverbs 27:19; II Corinthians 3:18 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">May we continue to trust and receive and grow in Him for who He really is...We have received a mere glimpse of our God’s character and how He wants His character instilled in us that He may live through us to others.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Where we have tended the tree and are waiting on the master for fruit to present itself may we hold fast that the Lord has begun a good work and He will see it to fruition.  This is a promise from His Word.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Question on day one was “What is your perspective of who God is.”
                                                                            Question on day fourteen “Has the Holy Spirit revealed a deeper perspective to grow from this day on...has He furrowed out chambers in your heart to remove any dross and mire you may have held on to? Has he brought to mind areas where you have held back? Are you willing to allow Christ full access to every chamber of Your heart that He may heal any broken perceptions that hold you back from knowing and trusting Him fully?
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Let us meditate on what the Holy Spirit has shown us and “Tend the tree and wait for the Master to exhibit the fruit.”  <b>HE WILL!</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">We have a glimpse of Our God who has always existed, ever-present, all powerful, all knowing, unchangeable, Supreme above all, full of wisdom, faithfulness, goodness, holiness, in all love and truthfulness.   This and more is the God we serve. He has a desire for each and everyone of us and has placed a call on all of  our lives...
                                                                            “The noise of a multitude in the mountains, Like that of many people! A tumultuous noise of the kingdoms of nations gathered together! <b>The LORD of hosts musters The army for battle.”</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">The call is to be a soldier for Christ.  <b>2 Timothy 2:3</b> and we need to be dressed for service and protection as we are in a real battle and it is fierce.
                                                                            “For we do not wrestle against flesh and blood, but against principalities, against powers, against the rulers of the darkness of this age, against spiritual hosts of wickedness in the heavenly places. Therefore we take up the whole armor of God, that we may be able to withstand in the evil day, and having done all, to stand.”
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Our next seven days we will examine the Armor of God that we may be reminded and regain our perspective on how to put on and maintain this armor for full service.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Father as we reflect on the these past fourteen days of fasting and praying may Your Spirit remind us of the convictions He has brought us to and may we take the steps spiritually to combat and correct wrong perceptions of who You are and who You desire to be in and through us.  May we all take steps to further understand and yield to the desires You have for us.  May this better understanding we have come to be demonstrated in our lives for your praise, honor and glory...and within these next seven days closing out our time of prayer and fasting may our hearts and minds continue to be open to be increased and refreshed within our Spirits and souls by You Holy Spirit for complete renewal.  In Jesus name...AMEN
                                                                        </p>

